🧠 Dataset Description

This dataset contains brain MRI images related to Parkinson’s disease, which can be used for building machine learning and deep learning models for medical image classification.

The dataset consists of approximately 830 MRI image files organized into folders.
Images represent brain scans that can be used to identify patterns associated with Parkinson’s disease.
The dataset is suitable for computer vision tasks such as:
Image classification
Feature extraction
Medical diagnosis using deep learning

Although the dataset does not provide a detailed official description, it is commonly used in research workflows involving MRI-based neurological disorder detection.

